REST application for taxi ordering
Project Description
This application is designed to simulate the work of a taxi ordering service. Users can register, place taxi orders, track order status, and rate service quality.
The application allows customers to quickly and conveniently order a taxi and for drivers to receive orders.

Functionality
User registration (clients and drivers);
Placing taxi orders;
Tracking order status;
Rating service quality;
User authentication;
User profile management;
Order management;
Management of driver and vehicle data.
Technologies
Java Spring Boot
Spring Core
Spring AOP
Spring Data JPA
Spring Security
Hibernate
OpenAPI (Swagger)
Database (MySQL)
JUnit for testing
Running the Application
Make sure you have Java 8+ and Maven installed.
Clone the project repository: git clone https://github.com/ZaizAU93/taxiGoApp.git
Navigate to the project folder: cd taxi
Configure the database connection in the application.properties file.
Run the application using the command: mvn spring-boot:run
API Documentation
Once the application is running, you can view the API documentation by visiting
http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui.html

